pr_review_comment_body:
We've generally tried to write our conditionals to be explicit in the following manner.

```python
if callable(thing):
    # do something
elif isinstance(thing, str):
    # do something
else:
    raise TypeError("<good error message indicating type not supported, what type was given, what types are allowed")
```

It ensures we don't hit weird cases where someone uses `bytes` or an `int` or something and our registry ends up with weird values.
